        "text": [
          " (عليه ‏السلام):"
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "17. Amīr al-mu’minīn, peace be upon him, was asked to explain the saying of the Messenger of Allāh: “Banish your old age (by hair-dye) and do not acquire resemblance to the Jews.” Amīr al-mu’minīn replied:"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1653,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
              "kind": "plain",
              "text": "إِنَّمَا قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/nahj-al-balagha:3:10:2",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/3/17/19",
        "text": [
          " (صلى‌ الله‌ عليه‌ وآله‌ وسلم) ذَلِكَ وَالدِّينُ قُلٌّ فَأَمَّا الْآنَ وَقَدِ اتَّسَعَ نِطَاقُهُ وَضَرَبَ بِجِرَانِهِ فَامْرُؤٌ وَمَا اخْتَارَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
            "The Prophet (S) said this at a time when the religion was confined to a few, but now that its expanse has widened and it is firmly settled everyone is free in his action. [1]"
          ]
        }
      }
